deer field
From Historic deerfield
Source "The Universal Cook or Lady's Complete Assistant" by John Towns end 1773
A modern Adaptation

Ingredients


3 1/2 cups flour
1 Tbsp ground ginger
1/2 tsp ground cloves
1 tsp ground mace
1 tsp ground nutmeg
1 1/2 tsp ground coriander seeds
1 1/2 tsp ground caraway seeds
1/2 cups molasses
1/2 cups brown sugar
1 cup melted butter
1 egg

Measure flour into a large bowl
Grate the nutmeg
Add the spices and whisk to combine 
Mix Molasses, sugar, butter, and egg in a small bowl
Add the wet ingredients to the dry ingredients, 1/3 at a time, mixing until the dough starts to form
Sprinkle some flour on a board and gently kneed the dough until it comes together
Set it aside to rest 20-30 minutes
Roll out the dough to about 1/8' thickness
Cut out into rounds or any shape you choose
Bake at 375 degrees F for 10-12 minutes
